text: Töss is a district in the city of Winterthur in Switzerland. It is District number 4. The district has these quarters: Schlosstal, Dättnau, Eichliacker and Rossberg. Until 1922 it was a municipality on its own. Then it became part of Winterthur. It is named after the river Töss which flows through the district. ==Other websites== Category:Former municipalities of Zürich Category:Winterthur
title: Töss (Winterthur)
